direct_enhancements.reason: Both methods generate ID numbers but with different validity outcomes (valid vs. invalid).
The generateInvalid method relies on isValidSwedishSsn to determine the validity of generated numbers.
Both generateInvalid and generateValid methods use calculateChecksum to validate or invalidate ID numbers.
The isValidSwedishSsn method, which generateInvalid relies on, uses parseDate to validate date parts of the ID number.
The generateInvalid method uses getPattern to generate random patterns for invalid ID numbers.
